<TITLE> Uncover Peelkhana events to secure country: BNP </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 15 (bdnews24.com)  BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain said Sunday the country would not be safe if the Pilkhana events were not uncovered. He censured the government ministers for their comments on the mutiny in BDR headquarters while the investigations were ongoing. "It may influence the investigation," he said at a rally organised by the party's volunteers' front Jatiyatabadi Swechchasebak Dal at Muktangan in the city. The rally demanded proper inquiry into the bloodbath at the BDR headquarters and protest the 'demolition' of BNP founder Ziaur Rahman's portrait in Chittagong
